page.title: 05Carn Les Boel (Bosistow Hd.)
page.content: Carn Les Boel, the headland to the south of Nanjizal has an island{bird {breeding sanctuary}close to the cliff. In the nesting season there are scores of{gulls, guillemots and shags nests on it. In June, when we were there, only about ten nests could be seen. The baby seagulls looked just like a little bit of fluff from where we were watching. Their mothers were very careful not to knock them off the cliff. They feed the young with fish. The most interesting part was seeing {cormorants and shags diving}into the water. In the sea just beyond the sanctuary a big{grey seal}was swimming and basking in the sun.{Carn Les Boel is known to RSPB members as a place {where migrant birds can be seen}in spring and autumn as they reach land after travelling across the English Channel.
